    "body" : "<p>Yes, from <a href=\"http://maven.apache.org/plugin-developers/index.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://maven.apache.org/plugin-developers/index.html</a>:</p>\n\n<p><em>What is a Mojo? A mojo is a Maven plain Old Java Object. Each mojo is an executable goal in Maven, and a plugin is a distribution of one or more related mojos.</em></p>\n\n<p>In short, a mojo is a maven goal, to extend functionality not already found in maven.</p>\n"
