    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As written <a href=\"http://books.sonatype.com/mvnref-book/reference/writing-plugins-sect-programming-maven.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here</a>:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>A Maven Plugin is a Maven artifact which contains a plugin descriptor\n  and one or more Mojos. A Mojo can be thought of as a goal in Maven,\n  and every goal corresponds to a Mojo. The <code>compiler:compile</code> goal\n  corresponds to the <code>CompilerMojo</code> class in the Maven Compiler Plugin,\n  and the <code>jar:jar</code> goal corresponds to the <code>JarMojo</code> class in the Maven\n  Jar Plugin. When you write your own plugin, you are simply grouping\n  together a set of related Mojos (or goals) in a single plugin\n  artifact.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>A Mojo simply associates with a Maven goal, so we can say a Mojo is much more than just a goal in Maven.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1875874,
      "reputation" : 75425,
      "user_id" : 1697099,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/gerXo.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Premraj",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1697099/premraj"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1516321301,
    "creation_date" : 1516321301,
    "answer_id" : 48332398,
    "question_id" : 8420561,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<ul>\n<li><p>MOJO (<strong>M</strong>aven <strong>O</strong>ld <strong>J</strong>ava <strong>O</strong>bject)  is a goal in Maven.    </p></li>\n<li><p>In maven, everything is done by plugin, a plugin has one or more related mojos i.e. goals.  </p></li>\n<li><p>Mojo is single unit of task in maven.  </p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>for example : <code>elicpse:eclipse</code> the eclipse plugin with eclipse goal is a MOJO</p>\n"
  } ],
